              <header class="style1">
                <h2>The Top Opioid Affected States: Pennsylvania</h2>
              </header>
              <a href="#" class="image featured"> <img src="../images/pennsylvania1.jpg"

                  alt="picture of Pennsylvania"> </a> <br>
              <p><b>Overdose Deaths</b></p>
              <p>In 2015, the state of Pennsylvania had a recorded 3,264
                overdoses that resulted in death, 42% (1,362) of those deaths
                were caused by opioid overdoses. </p>
              <p>A study from 2014 shows that the drug overdose deaths per
                100,000 people in that year was 21.9 compared to the 12.7 in
                2004. The number of drug overdose deaths in Pennsylvania have
                risen at an alarming rate, increasing nearly 14 fold in 35
                years. Painkillers and heroin addictions account for nearly half
                of all rehabilitation admissions and heroin abuse alone
                accounted for approximately 37.8% of those admissions.</p>
            </article>
            <a href="#" class="image featured"> </a>
            <div class="row 150%">
              <div class="4u 12u(mobile)">
                <section class="box">
                  <header><br>
                    <h2>Chester</h2>
                  </header>
                  <a href="#" class="image featured"><img src="../images/pennsylvania2.jpg"

                      alt="Picture of Chester"></a>
                  <p>As of July 2016, the town of Chester was deemed the most
                    dangerous city in Pennsylvania. The crime rates in the town
                    are more than five times the state-wide average and it has
                    more crimes on average than any other town in the state.</p>
                </section>
              </div>
              <div class="4u 12u(mobile)">
                <section class="box">
                  <header> <br>
                    <h2>Johnstown</h2>
                  </header>
                  <a href="#" class="image featured"><img src="../images/pennsylvania3.jpg"

                      alt="Picture of Johnstown"></a>
                  <p>Johnstown ranks in the top 10% in number of residents on
                    welfare, number of high school dropouts as well as payday
                    loans per capita.</p>
                </section>
              </div>
              <div class="4u 12u(mobile)">
